    "Case (ii): each layer intersects V cyc,k, with |V cyc,k | ≤ (κ -1)γ.",
    "Since in this case each layer intersects V cyc,k, it follows from the definition of the graph that each node v in V cyc \\ V cyc,k is connected to V cyc,k by at least two edges corresponding to nodes of V cyc,k in the previous layer and in the following layer of that of v. As a consequence,",
    "we can apply the same arguments as in Case (i) and (ii), switching the role of V cyc,k and V ′.",
    "Accordingly, |E ↑ cyc,k | ≥ 2γ, and the proof of Lemma 4.1 is complete.",
